<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="130" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Personal.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                    1895</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Baron Fava</hi>:</p>
                        <p>I have received your personal note, undated, filed in this Department on
                            the 18th instant, relative to the indigent condition of the families of
                            the Italians lynched in Colorado, and beg to say in reply that the
                            matter has been referred to the governor of Colorado for his
                            consideration.</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>